modules.description: Provides conversion functions between JS Promises and Lwt Promises, along with utilities to chain and handle asynchronous operations. Works with JS.Promise.t and Lwt.t types, enabling interoperability between JavaScript and OCaml asynchronous code. Enables seamless integration of browser-based asynchronous APIs with OCaml's Lwt-based concurrency model.

Converts between JavaScript and Lwt promises, handling error wrapping and unwrapping. Supports serialization and deserialization of values between OCaml and JavaScript using custom conversion functions. Enables interoperability in environments where JavaScript promises are used alongside OCaml's Lwt library.
